<div class="d-flex justify-content-center col-md-4 offset-md-4 my-5">
  <%= link_to "PLEASE SUPPORT YOUR CHURCH; DONATE NOW!", new_donation_path, class: "btn btn-primary btn-lg text-white" %>
  </div>
  <div class=row>
    <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12 main-body pe-5">
      <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
        <%= cl_image_tag("FrTomPentecost2021Scaled_qzwtu5", width:"100%") %>
        </div>
        <h1>We follow Jesus Christ...</h1>
        <h2>...whether we stay at home or join in public worship</h2>
        <%= image_tag("https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/saintpaulsnaplesorg/logos/Cross.png", width:"200",
          class: "float-start img-fluid pr-2" ) %>
          <p>All are welcome to join us in person Sunday mornings at 8 or 10 a.m. Please follow the latest
            recommendations of the CDC to keep yourself and your neighbors (i.e., every human being) safe.</p>
          <p>Otherwise, join us at 10 a.m. Sundays on YouTube, using your smart phone, computer or television set, <%= link_to "by clicking here" , "#{@worship.url}" %></p>
          
          <div class="clearall"></div>

          <% if @bulletin.url.present? %>
            <p><strong><%= link_to "Here is the bulletin for #{@bulletin.date.strftime(" %A, %b %d")}", "#{@bulletin.url}" %></strong></p>
          <% else %>
            <p>Sunday's bulletin will be available here on Thursday.</p>
          <% end %>

          <p>To learn about our worship service and about the<strong> <em>Episcopal Church,</em></strong> <%=link_to "click here", worship_index_path %>. And click on that shelf of red books to get a short, cute introduction to our time-honored <em>Book of Common Prayer.</em></p>
          
          <p><%= link_to "Click here for the on-line Book of Common Prayer",
              "https://www.churchpublishing.org/siteassets/pdf/book-of-common-prayer/book-of-common-prayer-2006.pdf"%></p>
          <div class="clearfix"></div>
          <p><strong><%= link_to "Click here for Scripture Readings" ,"http://www.lectionarypage.net" %></strong> </p>

          <h2 class="mt-3">Sacred Ground Series</h2>
            <p>This is a series of videos, readings and small-group discussions about race. This is highly recommended if you have questions about "critical race theory," a topic needlessly politicized. To watch an introduction, <%= link_to "click here. " , "https://www.episcopalchurch.org/sacred-ground/" %> <br>
          If you are interested in participating in a small group study and discussion at St. Paul's, <%=link_to "click here." , new_participant_path %></p>

          <h2 class="mt-3">Five questions of baptism</h2>
            <p><strong>Fr. Tom </strong> delivered a workshop for the Diocese of Southwest Florida entitled, <em>"Baptismal Covenant: Five Questions."</em> It can be viewed by clicking <%=link_to "this link" , "https://www.dioswfl.org/tv.html" %> any time. Fr. Tom is well acquainted with the sacrament of Baptism, as he focused on it in the pursuit of his doctorate from Seabury-Western.</p>

          <%= cl_image_tag("FarmMarketLogoOutreach2_up8pqz.png", class: "mx-auto d-block my-5" , width: "50%" ) %>
          
          <h2 class="mt-3">Home of the great Farmers' Market</h2>
          <h2> (The market will not be open Christmas or New Years days)</h2>
            <p>Welcome to the easy in-and-out St. Paul's Farmer's Market! Stop by the hospitality pit and introduce yourself to new friends and have a hot dog, on us! The market is now open, through next April, Saturdays from 8 a.m.to noon. Browse and buy books, jewelery and lots of produce.</p>
            <p>For more information about the market, <%= link_to "click here." , markets_index_path %></p>
            <div class="clearall"></div>
                  
            <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of these children</h2>
              <%=cl_image_tag("25_aeyuf2.jpg", width: "420" , height: "315" , class:"float-start pe-3") %>
              <p>Episcopalians of the Naples Deanery have been supporting the children at a shelter in the Dominican Republic for the last 18 years. The <em>Albergue el Buen Samaritano</em> in San Francisco de Macoris, serves a hundred children who would be on the street were it not for the shelter. The kids arrive for breakfast, learn their abcs and social skills and get lots of love that may otherwise be missing in their young lives. It is a ministry of love and
              affection, above all.</p>
              <div class="clearfix"></div>
                    
            <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of Tumaini Fund</h2>
              <%= cl_image_tag("SusanWilson_dvvx0e.jpg", width: "60%" , class: "float-end ms-3" ) %>
              <p>Dr. Susan Wilson, an English family physician, is full of energy and zealfor the Lord. She founded <em>Tumaini </em>(the word means "hope") <em> Fund </em> to put her faith to work in the AIDS-ravaged Kagera region of Northwest Tanzania. There she established an orphanage for thousands of children who lost their moms and dads to AIDS. In addition to monitary contributions, the ladies of our church, the ECW (Episcopal Church Women) have sewn numerous dresses, as seen here with Dr. Wilson.</p>
              <p>Parishioners Mike Moore and Roger Conant are directors for the fund in the United States.</p>
              <div class="clearfix"></div>
                    
              <h2 class="mt-3">Supporters of 'ERD'</h2>
                <%= link_to image_tag("https://www.episcopalrelief.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/logo.png", alt:"Episcopal Relief &amp; Development", width: '404' , crop: "scale", class: "d-block mx-auto" ), "https://episcopalrelief.org/" %>
                <p class="mt-3">Episcopal Relief and Development is a charity you can trust to use your resources wisely and lovingly. Click the logo above to learn more and make a donation.</p>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <%= image_tag("https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/saintpaulsnaplesorg/GodLovesNoException.png", width:"95%", class: "d-block mx-auto mt-5" , fetch_format: "auto" ) %>

      </div>
      <!--main-body -->

      <div class="col col-md-4 col-sm-8 px-4" style="background-color: #e2e2e2;">
        <p class="text-center"> <%= Date.current.strftime("%A, %B %e, %Y") %></p>
        <%= cl_image_tag("logos/update.png", width: "100%" ) %>
        
        <h2 class="mt-3">All the links</h2>
        <p><strong><%= link_to "Sunday worship service, 9 a.m." , "#{@worship.url}" %>
          </strong> Stream on your smart phone, computer or television. Subscribe to our YouTube channel using this link.</p>
        <% if @bulletin.url.present? %>
          <p><strong><%= link_to "Sunday bulletin" , "#{@bulletin.url}" %></strong></p>
        <% else %>
          <p><strong> Sunday's bulletin will be linked here on Thursday</strong></p>
        <% end %> <p><strong>
          <%= link_to "Wednesday evening bible study, 6:30 p.m.", "#{@evening_bible.url}" %>
            </strong> For the next several weeks we will be examining the meaning and impact of certain words in the Bible. Up next?: "Hell." Join us in person in the library or through the internet.</strong></p>
        <p><strong><%= link_to "Thursday wine time, 5:30 p.m.", "#{@wine.url}" %>
          </strong> This is a popular and relaxing chat room open to everyone who wishes to join in. Usually called "Thursday wine time," <strong>it's on Friday </strong> when the vestry meets, usually on the third Thursday of the month.</p>
        <p><strong>Join us for coffee </strong> after the Sunday morning worship service. It's a time for fellowship and to meet new friends. Parishioners bring snacks to share, and there's always plenty for everyone.</p>        
        <%= link_to cl_image_tag("#{@pathway.image}", width: "99%" ), "#{@pathway.link}" %>
        <p><strong>New Pathways available </strong> Click on the image above to read or download the latest edition (<%= @pathway.pubdate.strftime("%B %Y") %>) of <em>Pathways,</em> the parish newsletter.</p>
        <p><strong>Previous editions of <em>Pathways</em><%= link_to "can be found here" , pathways_path %> </strong></p><br>
        <%= cl_image_tag('togetherLogo_grjbrm.png', width: '95%' , class: 'image-center') %>
        <p><strong>There's a place for you</strong> to exercise your ministry at Saint Paul's! We are the hands and feet of the Risen Lord in the modern world that is in great need. Some of our ministries are <%= link_to "listed here." , opportunities_path %></p>
        <p class="mt-3">Wearing your <strong> name tag </strong> is an act of hospitality! We want visitors and our members to feel comfortable at services and coffee hour. If you don't have a name tag, call the office during the week to get one.</p>
      <%= cl_image_tag("1912588_wbdabz.png", width: "40%", class: "mt-3 image-center") %>
    
        <p class="mt-3"><strong>Get the Weekly Update in your email box </strong>
          <%= link_to "by signing up here.",'https://visitor.r20.constantcontact.com/d.jsp?llr=ip9lo9eab&p=oi&m=1104694077928&sit=ywgju8zfb&f=515707c1-0d44-46a0-803a-2fcb34db78a2'%></p>
        <%=link_to cl_image_tag("Calendar-clip_zbdtul.jpg", width: "55%" , class: "mt-3 mx-auto d-block", :fetch_format=> :auto), pages_calendar_path %>
      <h3>Click calendar to see our activities</h3>
    <div class="mt-3">
      <h2>Episcopal News Service</h2>
      <% @ens_feed.each do |feed| %>
        <h5> <%= link_to "#{feed.title}" , feed.url %></h5>
        <p><%= feed.summary.gsub(/[&#8230;]/, '...' ) %></p>
      <% end %>
    </div><!-- newsfeed -->
  </div><!--sidebar -->
  
</button>  

  </div><!-- row -->
</div><!-- container -->